---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="How to cite · America's School Trust Library"
      description="Citation guidance for America's School Trust Library and its component works."
    />
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen bg-archive-paper text-ink" data-source-id="about-cite">
    <Header />
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-prose p-4 sm:p-8">
      <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-a:text-blue-700 prose-a:underline">
        <h1>How to cite</h1>
        <p class="kicker">Placeholder citation guidance. A fuller style guide will follow.</p>

        <h2>The library</h2>
        <p>
          Cite this library as: <em>America's School Trust Library</em>, [year accessed]. <a href="https://schooltrusts.net">https://schooltrusts.net</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>State dossiers</h2>
        <p>
          For specific state dossiers, cite the entry path. Example: <em>America's School Trust Library, "Oregon," accessed 2026-05-04.</em> <a href="https://schooltrusts.net/reading/us-or/">https://schooltrusts.net/reading/us-or/</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>The Sacred Compact white paper</h2>
        <p>
          Cite the Sacred Compact as: Sullivan &amp; Bird, <em>Sacred Compact</em> (May 2026, version 5.0).
        </p>

        <h2>The booklet</h2>
        <p>
          Cite the underlying booklet as: Sullivan &amp; Bird, <em>Schools of the Republic</em> v1.3 (2025).
        </p>

        <h2>Corrections</h2>
        <p>
          Found a citation that needs work, or a source that should be in the bibliography? File an issue at <a href="https://github.com/dave-schooltrustlands/schooltrustlands-encyclopedia/issues">the project repository</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
